widgets_values:
Optional:

since this is inpainting, it's a good idea to use differential diffusion.

Many different options possible here.

1. No controlnet.
You can completely discard this controlnet, if you decrease the denoising strength on the ksampler.

2. Tile controlnet
With a high scaled soft weights, it will allow the image to change a lot while still maintaining most of its low frequency freatures (like head position, and most of the expression)

3. Inpaint controlnet
Same as tile controlnet, but more features of the original face are preserved. In that case, notice you connect the cropped images directly, without any Inpaint Preprocessor node.

4. Something else
For example mediapipe controlnet, openpose, or anything you can imagine. You are free to do whatever you want.

nodes.title: IMPORTANT - regarding controlnet
widgets_values:
You can use any controlnet, any combination of controlnet, ipadapters, or anything you like.

But, if you want to do **animations**, you want to use the following node to apply your controlnets: Apply Advanced ControlNet 🛂🅐🅒🅝

The regular controlnet cannot handle animations.
You really want to feather the mask, in case detected the mask overflows the cropped image. Otherwise, if this happens you will see a sharp edge where the mask overflowed.

mask:

it will only detect faces that are not masked.
Of course, you can change this behavior by using a InvertMask node.



threshold:

this is the usual yolov threshold used for face detection. 0.5 is the default, but most detected faces have a score higher than 0.7



min_size, max_size:

it will only detect faces whose bounding box edge sizes is between min_size and max_size.
